05:00.780 --> 05:06.200
Some designers would feel a massive productivity boost thanks to that.

05:06.200 --> 05:11.240
You can call it auto layout, smart layout, fancy layout, whatever.

05:11.240 --> 05:18.320
They could not have this once they were exposed to that.

05:18.320 --> 05:24.320
It's like not having this once you know about this intelligent layout system is like going

05:24.320 --> 05:28.960
really back in time and having to do everything manually.

05:28.960 --> 05:39.120
So the problem with this, as we thought at PEM port, was that unfortunately, these layout

05:39.120 --> 05:49.240
systems were design-centric, which is not bad per se, but was not developer-friendly.

05:49.240 --> 05:55.840
Basically it was not team-friendly, meaning designers would do their smart layout system

05:55.840 --> 06:00.500
and then all the vocabulary and the ideas, the abstractions were just for designers to

06:00.500 --> 06:02.320
understand and to enjoy.

06:02.320 --> 06:11.640
And then developers would go there and say, I need to translate this into code.

06:11.640 --> 06:16.040
Let's hope there's no issues, but there were issues.

06:16.040 --> 06:20.560
Not only technical issues, but also friction issues like back and forth.

06:20.560 --> 06:22.480
This, am I in control?

06:22.480 --> 06:23.960
No, I'm not.

06:23.960 --> 06:26.840
Neither the designer nor the developer.

06:26.840 --> 06:31.560
They would feel like they would have to constantly double check, double check.

06:31.560 --> 06:37.320
And you don't scale up your design or your code if you have to do that.

06:37.320 --> 06:43.320
PEM port came with a completely different approach and said, what if we have code-first

06:43.320 --> 06:45.180
